
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to construct a SQL statement by concatenating various string components. It uses the [set-value] slot to update the value of the [.sql] node. The [strings.concat] slot is employed to concatenate the current value of [.sql] with a double quote, a column name, another double quote followed by a space, and a column type, all retrieved using [get-value] from the [.arguments] node. This process effectively builds a SQL column definition string.
set-value:x:@.sql
   strings.concat
      get-value:x:@.sql
      .:"\""
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/columnName
      .:"\" "
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/columnType
